      "body_md": "**Windows Deployment Completion** — full notes attached below as `RELEASE-NOTES-v2.3.0.md`.\n\nCompletes the Windows deployment story: the **Content Builder** now installs as a **native Windows Service** (like the console since v2.2.0), so both platform components run on Windows Server / a Windows workstation with no Linux VM, Docker, or manual Python setup. Validated end to end on Windows Server 2022.\n\n### Artifacts (all self-contained, signed)\n- `audittoolkit-weardian-2.3.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz` — Linux console\n- `audittoolkit-weardian-2.3.0-windows-x86_64.zip` — Windows console (native service)\n- `sentry-content-builder-bundle-0.5.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz` — Content Builder (Linux)\n- `audittoolkit-content-builder-0.5.0-windows-x86_64.zip` — **Content Builder (native Windows service) — new**\n- SBOM + vulnerability report per Linux bundle; `.asc` signatures; signed `SHA256SUMS*`.\n\nBoth Windows bundles are built + signed + attached by CI (signing on Linux; no signing material on the Windows runner). There is **no MSI** — ZIP + PowerShell installer.\n\n### Verify\n`gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.asc SHA256SUMS` (key `1AA413CA5B8F5229`), then `sha256sum -c SHA256SUMS`; verify `SHA256SUMS-windows` and `SHA256SUMS-content-builder-windows` the same way.\n\nNo DB migration; licensing unchanged from v2.2.0.",
